    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d5f18ebe14c3308a",
      "text": "When we are looking for a solution, a new perspective, or an untapped resource, sometimes the search can be long and we can lose heart. Thinking laterally as a resource for problem solving also means that we look at the relationship between searching and finding in surprising and new ways."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "77012111e7299198",
      "text": "If to our old belief system the assumption should have belonged that we must not have searched long and hard stubbornly enough if we have not come yet to the goal, then suitable wise lateral thinkers convey to us perhaps the following idea:"
    },
